![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/5621904b-d111-42c8-9779-5ffe45d85689/Screenshot_20240412_140618.jpg?format=original)

World Wrestling Entertainment has unveiled an electrifying lineup of triple threat matches set to take place tonight. With high stakes on the line, these bouts are poised to determine the first challenger for Cody Rhodes' coveted WWE Championship.

The first showdown features a showdown of veteran prowess as Kevin Owens, Rey Mysterio, and AJ Styles step into the ring to prove their mettle. Owens, known for his brute strength and resilience, will undoubtedly bring his A-game as he looks to secure a path to championship gold. Mysterio, the high-flying luchador with decades of experience under his belt, promises to dazzle fans with his acrobatic prowess and signature maneuvers. Meanwhile, Styles, the "Phenomenal One," is poised to showcase his unmatched agility and technical prowess as he seeks to assert his dominance in the squared circle.

In the second triple threat match, the intensity reaches a fever pitch as LA Knight, Bobby Lashley, and Santos Escobar prepare to do battle. Knight, the brash and outspoken newcomer, aims to make a statement by taking down two of WWE's most formidable competitors. Lashley, the imposing powerhouse known for his raw athleticism and devastating spear, is poised to unleash his fury as he sets his sights on championship glory once more. And then there's Escobar, the cunning and calculating leader of Legado del Fantasma, who will stop at nothing to seize the opportunity to ascend to the top of the WWE hierarchy.

The stakes couldn't be higher as the winners of each triple threat match will go head-to-head next Friday to determine who will be the first challenger for Cody Rhodes' WWE Championship. With the prestige and honor of a championship opportunity hanging in the balance, these superstars will leave no stone unturned in their quest for victory.